{
  "texts": [
    "Our results help bridge this gap.",
    "We find that the Information Scrambling Index, measured in the middle layers, is strongly associated with the final NC geometry in ViT-S/B/L in our experiments, and provides a mechanistic perspective on why the computationally more efficient ViT-B attains a more favorable structure than the deeper, less efficient ViT-L.",
    "Having introduced the Cliff-Plateau-Climb pattern in Figure 1, we now examine each of its three phases in more detail.",
    "We combine layer-wise observations from standard pretrained models with targeted interventions to develop a mechanistic interpretation of each phase.",
    "Taken together, these results suggest an end-to-end picture of how Vision Transformers organize representations from initial patch embeddings to final class predictions in our setting."
  ]
}